---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
const personalSite = 'https://timothyjordan.com';
const repoUrl = 'https://github.com/timothyjordan/a14y';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About · a14y"
  description="a14y is built by Timothy Jordan — an expert on agent-led growth and agent readability, with a foundation in developer relations. About the maker and the thesis behind the open spec."
  wide
>
  <section class="hero" aria-labelledby="hero-heading">
    <div class="hero-text">
      <div class="eyebrow">
        <span class="eyebrow-pin">about</span>
        <span>the maker · the thesis</span>
      </div>
      <h1 id="hero-heading">Hi, I'm Timothy.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        I'm an expert on agent-led growth and agent readability,
        with a foundation in developer relations. Everyone keeps
        asking me about this, and lots of folks have ideas — so
        a14y is the consistent open-source spec we can all update
        together that tells you what to do.
      </p>
      <div class="cta-row">
        <a class="btn btn--primary" href={personalSite} rel="noopener">
          Hire me for advising →
        </a>
        <a class="btn btn--ghost" href={`${base}/spec/`}>
          Read the spec →
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <aside class="agent-panel" aria-label="Career snapshot">
      <pre class="agent-output" aria-label="whoami output"><span class="ag-prompt">%</span> whoami
Timothy Jordan — DevRel · agent-led growth

  <span class="ag-pass">✓</span> 16y  Google — DevRel, OSS strategy
         Flutter · Firebase · Angular · Dart
         TensorFlow · Material · Maps · Search
  <span class="ag-pass">✓</span> ~2y  Vercel — VP of Developer Experience
         AI-driven DevRel · Agent-Led Growth
  <span class="ag-pass">✓</span> now  a14y maintainer · advising

<span class="ag-prompt">%</span> contact --advising
→ <span class="ag-mute">timothyjordan.com</span></pre>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <hr class="section-rule" aria-hidden="true" />

  <section class="section section--tight" aria-labelledby="why-open-heading">
    <div class="section-head">
      <h2 id="why-open-heading">Why a14y is open</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">
        Agents already read most of the web before humans do. Every
        team trying to be readable to them is reinventing the same
        checklist in a private wiki. That doesn't scale, and it
        doesn't converge.
      </p>
    </div>
    <p>
      The spec is versioned and the scorecard is frozen per release,
      so historical scores stay comparable as the field moves. The
      engine that scores any URL is the same one that scores
      a14y.dev itself — every page on this site has to pass its own
      checks. If you have a check we should add, or you disagree
      with one we already have, the repo is the room: open an issue
      or a PR.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="working-on-heading">
    <div class="section-head">
      <h2 id="working-on-heading">What I'm working on</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">
        Three concrete artifacts and a small amount of advising on
        the side.
      </p>
    </div>
    <ul class="about-list">
      <li>
        <strong>The spec and scorecard.</strong> Three layers
        (discoverability, parsing, comprehension) operationalised as
        pass-or-fail checks. Versioned so a score from last quarter
        still means something next quarter.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>The tools.</strong> A CLI, a Chrome extension, and
        a coding-agent skill that all run the same checks against
        the same scorecard. Output a human report, JSON, or a
        Markdown fix-list ready to hand to an agent.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Advising.</strong> Helping teams measure and improve
        agent readability across docs, marketing, and product
        surfaces — and bring agent-led growth into how they ship.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="hire-heading">
    <div class="section-head">
      <h2 id="hire-heading">Work with me</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">
        Advising on developer relations, agent-led growth, and
        agent-readability strategy. The full services page and
        contact details live on my personal site.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="cta-row">
      <a class="btn btn--primary" href={personalSite} rel="noopener">
        Hire me →
      </a>
      <a class="btn btn--ghost" href={repoUrl} rel="noopener">
        Or contribute on GitHub →
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .about-list {
      max-width: 64ch;
      padding-left: 0;
      list-style: none;
      display: grid;
      gap: 14px;
    }
    .about-list li {
      padding: 14px 16px;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: var(--radius-md, 10px);
      background: var(--surface);
      line-height: 1.6;
    }
    .about-list strong {
      color: var(--text);
      font-weight: 600;
      margin-right: 0.35em;
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
